ustomizing the view.","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In general, use the various "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Keyboard\/State"},{"type":"text","text":" contexts and their auto-persisted settings to control the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardView"},{"type":"text","text":", and use the view builders and apply view modifiers to make app-specific customizations."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The standard emoji keyboard and collapsed view are unlocked by "},{"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"KeyboardKit Pro","type":"text"}],"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardKitPro","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"KeyboardKit Pro"},{"type":"text","text":". You can however inject any custom views you like."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"…customize the keyboard behavior","level":3,"anchor":"customize-the-keyboard-behavior"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The easiest way to customize the behavior of the keyboard is to inherit ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardAction\/StandardActionHandler"},{"text":", then customize the behavior of any ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Keyboard\/Gesture"},{"text":" on any ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardAction"},{"text":" by overriding the various service functions, like ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Key